726413f-a.title: Queens: Corona Avenue - 92nd Street
726413f-a.text:
Corona Avenue, north side, between 92nd and 93rd Streets, showing the Ludlow House, erected about 1780. In the rear is
the factory of the Durkee Company.
View 1: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  1922
View 2:  P. L. Sperr  June 7, 1927

726415f-c.title: Queens: Corona Avenue - 92nd Street
726415f-c.text:
Corona Avenue (formerly Union Avenue, also known as Alstyne Avenue) north side, between 92nd and 93rd Streets, showing in 4 views the Ludlow farmhouse erected about 1780 on Commons Tract. John R. Ludlow married Catalina Ditmars. Other owners were W. Card 1860; Isaac C. Card later, arnd Samuel Lord in 1873. The house was in ruins on June 28, 1930 and was rased by Oct. 1930.
1922
Views 1 and 2
Views 354: May 1923
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
